### LangChain4j Demo - Test Requests

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### ============================================
### Demo Endpoints
### ============================================

### Get Demo Info
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/info

### Run All Demos (This will take a minute)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/demo/all

### ============================================
### Simple Chat Endpoints
### ============================================

### Simple Chat - Basic Question
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What is LangChain4j in one sentence?"
}

### Simple Chat - Technical Question
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "Explain Java Streams API"
}

### Chat with System Message
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/system
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "systemMessage": "You are a helpful Java expert. Be concise and technical.",
  "userMessage": "What is Spring Boot?"
}

### ============================================
### AI Assistant Endpoints
### ============================================

### AI Assistant Chat
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/assistant
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What are the benefits of using microservices?"
}

### Greet User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/greet
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Alice"
}

### Translate to Spanish
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/translate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "text": "Hello, how are you today?",
  "language": "Spanish"
}

### Translate to French
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/translate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "text": "Good morning, welcome to our application",
  "language": "French"
}

### Translate to German
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/translate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "text": "Thank you for using our service",
  "language": "German"
}

### ============================================
### RAG Endpoints
### ============================================

### Ingest Sample Documents - Java & Spring
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "documents": [
    "Java is a high-level, class-based, object-oriented programming language. It was developed by Sun Microsystems and released in 1995. Java applications are compiled to bytecode that can run on any Java Virtual Machine (JVM).",
    "Spring Boot is an open-source Java framework that simplifies the development of production-ready applications. It provides auto-configuration, embedded servers, and starter dependencies to reduce boilerplate code.",
    "LangChain4j is a Java library that makes it easy to integrate Large Language Models into Java applications. It provides abstractions for common LLM patterns like chat, embeddings, and RAG.",
    "Maven is a build automation and project management tool for Java projects. It uses XML configuration (pom.xml) to manage dependencies, build lifecycle, and project structure.",
    "Microservices architecture is a design approach where applications are built as a collection of small, independent services. Each service runs in its own process and communicates via lightweight protocols like HTTP."
  ]
}

### Ingest Sample Documents - AI & ML
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "documents": [
    "RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) is a technique that combines information retrieval with text generation. It retrieves relevant documents from a knowledge base and uses them as context for the LLM to generate more accurate responses.",
    "Vector embeddings are numerical representations of text that capture semantic meaning. They are created by neural networks and enable semantic search by finding similar content based on meaning rather than exact keyword matches.",
    "Large Language Models (LLMs) are AI models trained on vast amounts of text data. They can understand and generate human-like text, perform various NLP tasks, and reason about complex topics.",
    "Prompt engineering is the practice of designing effective prompts to get desired outputs from LLMs. It involves crafting clear instructions, providing context, and using techniques like few-shot learning.",
    "Token is the basic unit of text that LLMs process. A token can be a word, part of a word, or punctuation. Most LLMs have a maximum context window measured in tokens (e.g., 4096, 8192, or 128000 tokens)."
  ]
}

### Query RAG - About Java
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What is Java?"
}

### Query RAG - About Spring Boot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What is Spring Boot and what are its benefits?"
}

### Query RAG - About RAG
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "Explain RAG and how it works"
}

### Query RAG - About Vector Embeddings
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What are vector embeddings?"
}

### Query RAG - About LangChain4j
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What is LangChain4j used for?"
}

### Query RAG - About Microservices
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": "What is microservices architecture?"
}

### Get RAG Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/stats

### ============================================
### Test Sequence for Demo
### ============================================

### 1. First, ingest some documents
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest (use one of the above)

### 2. Then query without RAG to see the difference
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple

### 3. Finally query with RAG to see improved response
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query

### ============================================
### Error Testing
### ============================================

### Test Empty Message
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/simple
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": ""
}

### Test Missing Question
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/query
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "question": ""
}

### Test Empty Documents
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rag/ingest
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "documents": []
}